ğŸ“˜ Explanation of Each Component
ğŸ“ src/

Contains all Java .java source files.

âœ” Interface

ConverterService.java
Defines the method:

double convert(double amount, String from, String to);

âœ” Custom Exception

InvalidCurrencyException.java
Handles invalid user currency input.

âœ” Abstraction + Inheritance

RateProvider.java â€” Abstract class
StaticRateProvider.java â€” Child class that loads static currency rates

âœ” Polymorphism

CurrencyConverter.java
Implements the interface and connects with the rate provider.

âœ” Data Model

ConversionRecord.java
Holds amount, from, to, result.

âœ” JDBC Layer

DBHelper.java
Creates MySQL connection using JDBC.

ConversionDAO.java
Inserts conversion records into database table.

âœ” Multithreading

LoggerThread.java
Prints conversion history asynchronously.

âœ” Main Application

SmartCurrencyConverter.java
Handles user input, conversions, DB save, threading, and history storage.

ğŸ“ lib/ Folder

Contains:

mysql-connector-j.jar


You must include this in classpath to run JDBC.

ğŸ“ database/ Folder

Contains:

converterdb.sql


This file includes:

CREATE DATABASE converterdb;

USE converterdb;

CREATE TABLE conversion_history (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    amount DOUBLE,
    source VARCHAR(10),
    target VARCHAR(10),
    result DOUBLE
);
